    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "True love is not a strong, fiery, impetuous passion. On the contrary, it is calm and deep in its nature. It looks beyond mere externals, and is attracted by qualities alone. It is wise and discriminating, and its devotion is real and abiding.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">7<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"2T 133.1\" data-link=\"120.553\">Testimonies for the Church 2:133</span>.</span></a></sup>",
