    "content": "There are persons who have for some time made a profession of religion who are, to all intents and purposes, without God and without a sensitive conscience. They are vain and trifling; their conversation is of a low order. <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"52\"></span> Courtship and marriage occupy the mind, to the exclusion of higher and nobler thoughts.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">10<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"4T 589.1\" data-link=\"114.2909\">Testimonies for the Church 4:589</span>.</span></a></sup>",
