    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 53.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Caution to a Youthful Student</strong>&mdash;You are now in your student&apos;s life; let your mind dwell upon spiritual subjects. Keep all sentimentalism apart from your life. Give to yourself vigilant self-instruction, and bring yourself under self-control. You are now in the formative period of character; nothing with you is to be considered trivial or unimportant which will detract from your highest, holiest interest, your efficiency in the preparation to do the work God has assigned you.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">14<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 23, 1893\" data-link=\"14058.7347001\">Letter 23, 1893</span>.</span></a></sup>",
